                          <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="partly" xml:id="binding">
                              <decoNote xml:id="b1">The book is sewn on two sewing stations (one pair) linked to wooden boards with a leather quarter cover.</decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="leather"/>
                        </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Boards">
                              The manufacture of the right board is more refined than the one of the left board. Along the outer edge of the right board there are inscriptions.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Cover">
                              The book has a leather quarter cover </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b5" type="SewingStations">2</decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b6">
                              For the link-stitch sewing a thread of <term key="vegetalThread" ana="#vegetalThread">vegetal origin</term> has been used.
                              </decoNote>
                              <decoNote xml:id="b7" type="Spine">
                              On the spine of the quires, close to the head and to the tail, there are small holes, probably used for quire tackets.
                              </decoNote>
                            </binding>
                          </bindingDesc>
